We recommended that the Local Chief Executive and the MDRRMO: 

a.) advice the LDRRMO to strictly follow the LDRRMFIP based on the four thematic areas to ensure that the entire Municipality is well prepared for acts of God and manmade disasters; 

b.) adopt sound measures to prevent and mitigate all kinds of risks on the eventuality of a disaster or calamity; 

c.)  keep in stock various medicines and commodities purchased under the 70% preparedness. Be sure that it may not immediately spoil and expires; and

d.) instruct the Municipal Accountant/Municipal Budget Officer/Municipal Treasurer, to promptly transfer the fund balance of the LDRRMF to the Special Trust Fund not later than December 31 of each year.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive to; 

 (a) cause the proper integration of the gender concerns of all offices into their respective Work and Financial Plan through gender analysis or gender mainstreaming in order to rationalize and widen the scope of the Programs/Projects/Activities (PAPs) in the ensuing years; and  

(b) advice the Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that the overall GAD Plan and the details of the approved GAD budget are harmonized with the WFP of all the offices/departments concerned.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive and the MENRO;                (a) continually involve the participation of the barangay officials in all environmental concerns;

(b) strictly enforce the implementation of the existing environmental laws and encourage constituents to abide and cooperate for the success of the program; and

(c) intensify information campaign on the mandatory segregation of wastes in every household.

Prioritize the implementation of the remaining projects under the 20% Development Fund;

Improve the procurement process; and

Ensure all programs/projects/activities incorporated in the annual budget of the Development Fund be fully implemented through proper planning.

We recommended to the Local School Board to:

Adhere to the guidelines provided by law in allocating the SEF budget  that will give priority to: construction of school buildings and facilities; repair and maintenance of school buildings and facilities; establishment and maintenance of extension classes; and sports activities;

Conduct surveys in different schools under the Municipality  to ensure that all concerns are considered in the prioritization of projects for possible inclusion in the preparation of the SEF budget;

Review the reasonableness and necessity of the amount provided for every expense item.  

Implement the repair and maintenance of school building programs in both the current and continuing appropriations.

